{"key":"processedPost-5340565","value":{"id":5340565,"first":5339824,"last":5340859,"when":1140975453,"utime":"02/26/06 07:37 PM","content":"Correct.  If you'll keep your master cultures in the refrigerator in test tubes, you can remove a very small piece once every few months to keep fresh material for growing.  Once a year, remove a small piece from the test tube, and let it grow in a petri dish for three days or so, then remove a small piece from the petri dish and use it to inoculate a fresh test tube.  If you'll do this, you can keep the same culture for twenty years or more without any problems from senesence.<br />RR","title":"Re: Substrain Development","forum":"Mushroom Cultivation"}}